00:41:12.520 --> 00:41:17.110
Recent research in
neuroscientific --

00:41:17.110 --> 00:41:22.020
recent neuroscientific research
has demonstrated how narrative

00:41:22.020 --> 00:41:27.100
in fiction activates
particular parts of the brain,

00:41:27.100 --> 00:41:30.120
including the sensory
and motor cortexes.

00:41:30.120 --> 00:41:34.260
In her summary of this research,
Annie Murphy Paul notes, the brain,

00:41:34.260 --> 00:41:37.780
it seems, does not make much of
a distinction between reading

00:41:37.780 --> 00:41:41.180
about an experience and
encountering it in real life.

00:41:41.180 --> 00:41:46.120 position:56%
In each case, the same
neurological regions are stimulated.

00:41:46.120 --> 00:41:47.680
One researcher, she reports,

00:41:47.680 --> 00:41:51.330
found that fiction offered readers
the opportunity to enter fully

00:41:51.330 --> 00:41:53.750
into other people's
thoughts and feelings.

00:41:53.750 --> 00:41:57.430
Another saw substantial overlap
in the brain networks used

00:41:57.430 --> 00:41:59.680
to understand stories
and the networks used

00:41:59.680 --> 00:42:02.710
to navigate interactions
with other individuals.

00:42:02.710 --> 00:42:05.980
In particular, interactions in
which we're trying to figure

00:42:05.980 --> 00:42:08.970
out the thoughts and
feelings of others.

00:42:08.970 --> 00:42:12.390
Other researchers suggest
reading fiction is an exercise

00:42:12.390 --> 00:42:14.740
that hones our real
life social skills

00:42:14.740 --> 00:42:17.850
and that regular fiction
readers seem to be better able

00:42:17.850 --> 00:42:20.680
to understand other
people, empathize with them,

00:42:20.680 --> 00:42:23.350
see the world from
their perspective.

00:42:23.350 --> 00:42:28.110
Fiction, notes Keith Oatley, is
a particularly useful simulation

00:42:28.110 --> 00:42:31.970 position:56%
because negotiating the social world
effectively is extremely tricking

00:42:31.970 --> 00:42:35.320
requiring us to weigh up
myriad interacting instances

00:42:35.320 --> 00:42:37.210
of cause and effect.

00:42:37.210 --> 00:42:40.600
Just as computer simulations
can help us get to grips

00:42:40.600 --> 00:42:45.120
with complex scientific
problems, so novels, stories,

00:42:45.120 --> 00:42:49.790
and dramas can help us understand
the complexities of social life.

00:42:49.790 --> 00:42:54.460
Do y'all remember what the Dewey
